name: beta-glucosidase
classes: Glycosidases, i.e. enzymes that hydrolyse O- and S-glycosyl compounds
reaction: Hydrolysis of terminal, non-reducing beta-D-glucosyl residues with release of beta-D-glucose
comment: Wide specificity for beta-D-glucosides. Some examples also hydrolyse one or more of the following: beta-D-galactosides, alpha-L-arabinosides, beta-D-xylosides, beta-D-fucosides.
